2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses resource allocation and network access problem to maximize the normalized throughput, which is related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The proposed learning-based framework involves Q-learning and game theory, which are related to systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions the quality-of-service requirements of incumbent WiFi users, which is related to multimedia. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper does not explicitly mention any security-related issues, but the coexistence mechanism for LAA-LTE based HetNets may have security implications, which is related to cryptography and security.
